Package de.uos.nbp.senhance

Interface Summary
EventLogger A Logger is used to persistently store data and events.
EventSink EventSink is the counterpart to EventSource and is a consumer of the events.
EventSource An EventSource is a class that will acquire (in the case of physical devices) or generate (in the case of, for example, simulators) data events.
 

Class Summary
DeviceListActivity This Activity appears as a dialog.
SDLogger A Logger that writes to SD card in CSV format.
 

Enum Summary
EventSource.DeviceState These are the coarse-grained states of the underlying device of the EventSource.
EventSource.UIEvent These event constants are used for communication with the user interface.
